review:
[h2]"Friendship is being there when someone’s feeling low and not being afraid to kick them." - R. K. Milholland[/h2]

[h2]Sum-Up[/h2]
[h3]In-depth analysis further down.[/h3]

 [td]

• An ideal choice for gatherings or bonding sessions with family and friends.
[/td]
 [td]
• Best enjoyed with company; not recommended for solo-play.
• While initially entertaining, it may lose its charm once the novelty wears off.
[/td]

 [td]

FPS: 75+

[table]
[tr]
 [td][b]🌌 Content & Replay Value[/b][/td]
 [td]You can play the game for as long as you desire, with a variety of maps and arenas to explore and activities to engage in. There are no unlockables since most content is readily available from the start, granting you full access to every option imaginable right from the beginning. This ensures unlimited playthroughs, though the game's replay value primarily lies in the joy of playing alongside your friends.[/td]
[/tr]
[tr]
 [td][b]💵 Is it worth buying? [/b] [/td]
 [td]Yes. But consider getting it at a discount.
[/td]
[/tr]
[tr]
 [td][b]🎮 Steam Deck Compatibility[/b] [/td]
[td]Can be played on the Steam Deck, so it's a perfect option if you wish.[/td]
[/tr]
[tr]
 [td][h3]🧾 Verdict: Good[/h3]
[url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2761784706] Rating Chart Here[/url]   
[/td]

 [td]While the game may not boast any exceptional qualities, it has a remarkable knack for turning every moment into a uniquely special and uproariously hilarious experience. The truth is, a game doesn't have to achieve a perfect 10/10 rating to provide endless fun. This particular game is tailor-made for gatherings or simply spending quality time with loved ones.[/td]
[/tr]
[/table]

[quote=TalePlay][i] Check our [url=https://store.steampowered.com/curator/38352719/] Curator Page [/url] for short reviews. If you wish to get more gaming listings, news, and reviews check our [url=https://www.youtube.com/@tale_play] Youtube [/url] channel as we release videos there often.[/i][/quote] 

[h2]In-depth[/h2] 
[h3]⚔️ Gameplay & Exploration: [/h3]  

Gang Beasts is a fighting game, where you either fight in teams or against each other. You have different types of game types. Arena, is the most common one, football and waves.

These are all fun to experience in groups of people and punch, kick, and head-bump in the most hilarious ways possible. This game will make you forget you're in a serious fight in seconds and just allow you to mash buttons, laugh out loud and just overall have a great time.

You have a large pool of areas to pick and choose and game modes to spice up the game however you and your friends want.

This game's quirky physics is what makes this game a total delight to play.

https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3183522191

[h3]😄 Fun: [/h3]

One of the best games to have fun in with. Whether you spend a few minutes or hours, this game will make sure you're having a blast all the time.

[h3]🏞 Visuals & Presentation: [/h3]  

Its graphics make it easy to distinguish characters, and places of interests, dangerous areas to avoid. It's cute characters are a delight to look at even under the most brutal circumstances where one gets knocked out or thrown in front of a train.

https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3183521990

[h3]🔊 Sound & Voice-Acting: [/h3]  

Though it may not seem extraordinary at first glance, the careless button mashing, punches, and kicks you land on characters infuse the gameplay with an irresistible blend of flair and punch, resulting in uproarious moments that are bound to leave you in stitches.

[h3]📖 Story & Writing: [/h3]  

None existent. This game focuses on gameplay.

https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3183522529

[h3]🧵 Length & Difficulty: [/h3]  

As lengthy or as short as you want it to be. It's a game you play today, forget about it, play a few months or years later and it's just as fun.

Not a difficult game at all, but with the right skill you can pretty much dominate the ring if you understand what you're doing.

[h3]⭕️Verdict: [/h3]  
Gang Beasts stands out as the ideal game for enjoying with friends and family. Its dynamic combat mechanics spawn uproarious moments that are difficult to replicate. While it may offer brief gameplay sessions, the laughter and enjoyment it delivers will be some of the most memorable experiences you'll ever have.

author: {'steamid': '76561198148801188', 'num_games_owned': 0, 'num_reviews': 9, 'playtime_forever': 27, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 8, 'playtime_at_review': 27, 'last_played': 1711746104}
review: Absolutely sucks. The opposite of intuitive controls. Even when I looked for the controls (hard to find them) and then learned them, they don't make any sense. Hit jump, you MIGHT jump, tap keys to move, you might move, grab? it's punch and hold i think? lift? is just lift your arms... there is no explanation for anything, no practice arena or way to learn. The UI / menus are absolutely not intuitive. I reset my input mappings like 3 times just trying to escape the menu with changes. Like, it feels like a 5th grader somehow made it, or was the development lead or wrote the requirements. TERRIBLE. feels like a free to play game that got cranked out in like 2 days for profit. Can't believe I spent money on this. I'd ask for it back if I could. AMAZED that the reviews are VERY POSITIVE. don't be fooled. it's insanely difficult to play. maybe that's what people like, but it should literally be called "Unplayable Game" so you know in advance you can't even count on the controls doing what they say they will. the videos make it look so easy but ti's not. nothing does what you expect. terrible. absolutely terrible.

author: {'steamid': '76561199144595994', 'num_games_owned': 94, 'num_reviews': 15, 'playtime_forever': 88, 'playtime_last_two_weeks': 0, 'playtime_at_review': 88, 'last_played': 1691792103}
review:
Gang Beasts: Un Torbellino de Diversión y Complicidad Familiar

Queridos amigos de la diversión y la camaradería, los invito a un viaje a través del emocionante mundo de Gang Beasts, visto a través de los ojos de un abuelo y su nieto, quienes encontraron un escape juguetón y lleno de risas en este juego mientras enfrentaban tiempos difíciles.

Gang Beasts nos sumerge en un caos de peleas alocadas y desafíos hilarantes, donde la risa y la competencia se combinan para crear momentos inolvidables de diversión en familia. Junto a mi amado nieto, nos lanzamos a las peleas callejeras más locas que hayamos experimentado, riendo a carcajadas mientras nuestros personajes se enfrentaban en una batalla tumultuosa por la supremacía.

Cada encuentro en Gang Beasts nos brindaba una oportunidad para fortalecer nuestro vínculo y crear recuerdos que perdurarán por siempre. Desde peleas en rascacielos hasta enfrentamientos en trenes en movimiento, cada escenario nos presentaba un nuevo desafío y una nueva oportunidad para compartir risas y complicidad.

Gang Beasts no solo nos ofreció diversión sin fin, sino también un espacio para explorar nuestra creatividad y trabajar en equipo. A través de cada pelea y cada desafío, aprendimos a confiar en el otro y a celebrar nuestras victorias juntos, fortaleciendo nuestro lazo familiar con cada momento compartido en el juego.

En resumen, Gang Beasts es mucho más que un simple juego; es una experiencia de complicidad y diversión familiar que nos permitió encontrar alegría incluso en los momentos más difíciles. A través de la risa y la camaradería, descubrimos un refugio donde el amor y la conexión florecieron, recordándonos que juntos podemos superar cualquier obstáculo que la vida nos presente.

Calificación: ★★★★★

Desde nuestras batallas en las calles hasta las risas en la pantalla, les invito a sumergirse en la experiencia llena de diversión y complicidad de Gang Beasts y a descubrir el poder del juego para unir a la familia en momentos de necesidad. Que este juego les traiga la misma alegría y conexión que ha brindado a mi nieto y a mí en nuestros momentos de dificultad.
